Burnless License

Copyright 2026 Custos-com (Burnless Authors)

Burnless uses a three-tier license model. Different parts of the
codebase are covered by different licenses depending on their purpose.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

TIER 1 — Apache License 2.0
Applies to: pkg/ schema/ examples/

The public SDK, sre.yaml schema, and examples are licensed under the
Apache License, Version 2.0. This allows anyone to build tooling,
integrations, and extensions on top of Burnless without restriction.

Full text: licenses/LICENSE-Apache-2.0
           http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

TIER 2 — GNU Affero General Public License v3 (AGPLv3)
Applies to: cmd/ internal/ deploy/ .github/

The core CLI, burn rate agent, Kubernetes operator, and all integrations
are licensed under AGPLv3. This means:

  FREE forever — including SSO, RBAC, and all CLI features.
  Self-hosting the agent and K8s operator: FREE.
  Running Burnless CLI at work: FREE, no restrictions.

  If you offer a hosted/managed Burnless service using modified code,
  you must release your source code under AGPLv3.

  If you embed Burnless in a proprietary commercial product for
  distribution, contact licensing@burnless.dev.

Full text: licenses/LICENSE-AGPLv3
           https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.txt

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

TIER 3 — Business Source License 1.1 (BSL)
Applies to: saas/ dashboard/ api-server/

The hosted SaaS dashboard and commercial features are licensed under
BSL 1.1. Source code is visible and readable. Free for development,
testing, and self-hosted use under 5 services.

Production SaaS use above 5 services requires a commercial licence.
Each BSL release automatically converts to Apache 2.0 after 4 years.

Full text: licenses/LICENSE-BSL
           https://burnless.dev/license

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Summary

  You are a SRE engineer using the CLI         → FREE (AGPLv3)
  You are self-hosting the agent + operator    → FREE (AGPLv3)
  You want SSO and RBAC                        → FREE (AGPLv3)
  You are building a plugin or integration     → FREE (Apache 2.0)
  You are using burnless.dev SaaS (dev/test)   → FREE (BSL)
  You are using burnless.dev SaaS (production) → PAID (BSL commercial)
  You want to offer managed Burnless yourself  → contact us

Contact: licensing@burnless.dev
Website: https://burnless.dev/license
